# defensive perm restore for /srv. Some apt postinst scripts
# (most likely systemd / dpkg / snapd postinsts) silently chmod /srv to
# 0750, which breaks every non-root process that needs to traverse to
# /path/to/workspace/* (training, llama-server, dashboards, …). Cheap fix:
# restore 0755 every minute. Idempotent.
* * * * * root /bin/chmod 755 /srv 2>/dev/null
